parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To run before, outrun, run in advance. From pro and trecho; to run forward, i.e. Outstrip, precede.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
From en and pros; in front of (literally or figuratively) or time).

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To go up, mount, ascend; of things: I rise, spring up, come up. From ana and the base of basis; to go up.
A sycamore tree. From sukon and moron; the 'sycamore'-fig tree.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: Properly, to stare at, i.e. to discern clearly; by extension, to attend to; by Hebraism, to experience; passively, to appear.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A strengthened form of melo; to intend, i.e. Be about to be, do, or suffer something.

parse: Verb - Present Infinitive Middle or Passive
str2: To pass through, spread (as a report). From dia and erchomai; to traverse.
That, that one there, yonder. From ekei; that one (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed.
